message.content: We refer to Wikipedia articles on medicine for help. The physical exam findings suggest skeletal dysplasia, and among the options, only mutation in the FGFR3 receptor is associated with skeletal dysplasia. Alpha-L iduronidase is associated with mucopolysaccharidosis, COL1A1 is associated with osteogenesis imperfecta, and SLC26A2 transporter is associated with diastrophic dysplasia.
